1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,496
[North of Thailand]

3
00:00:02,341 --> 00:00:04,380
In a faraway valley in
the north of Thailand

4
00:00:05,220 --> 00:00:08,940
there is a village situated
amidst undefiled nature,

5
00:00:09,830 --> 00:00:11,180
cut off from the outside world.

6
00:00:11,877 --> 00:00:15,620
A special tribe called
'Mudan' lives in this place.

7
00:01:24,037 --> 00:01:25,038
Gaysorn

8
00:01:25,970 --> 00:01:30,300
you are an heir of Mudan tribe.

9
00:01:31,540 --> 00:01:34,180
You are now 20 years old

10
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:38,020
and your body will be fragrant.

11
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:44,460
It's even more fragrant
than all the flowers.

12
00:01:44,899 --> 00:01:46,259
In this world,

13
00:02:12,383 --> 00:02:14,140
beautiful flowers come with danger.

14
00:02:14,530 --> 00:02:18,580
Greedy people will try
to benefit from your scent.

15
00:02:19,460 --> 00:02:20,980
You have to be careful.

16
00:02:21,613 --> 00:02:24,740
Don't trust the outsiders, ever.

17
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:47,400
"Flower Boy"
(Episode 1)

18
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,137
Good afternoon to our
honored guests and the press.

19
00:03:50,247 --> 00:03:53,377
Please welcome Mr. Wittaya Sukontawanich,

20
00:03:53,407 --> 00:03:56,087
chairman of Sukontawanich Company,

21
00:03:56,227 --> 00:03:59,528
and the executive of scented
products named 'Kusuma'.

22
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,497
It is well-known that our brand, Kusuma,

23
00:04:06,737 --> 00:04:08,257
a high-end perfume brand

24
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,937
is expanding to the global market.

25
00:04:10,657 --> 00:04:12,217
Our selling point is that

26
00:04:12,340 --> 00:04:15,377
the scent has been extracted
from true natural products.

27
00:04:15,897 --> 00:04:17,417
Despite the fact that these past years

28
00:04:17,814 --> 00:04:20,177
our company faced with
some difficulties such as

29
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:22,178
a revenue shortfall,

30
00:04:22,527 --> 00:04:24,417
I still believe that this year

31
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:26,417
Kusuma will come back and be great again

32
00:04:26,817 --> 00:04:30,217
under the supervision of our
new generation of executives.

33
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:32,297
I'd like to introduce

34
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,377
Mr. Phummarak Sukontawanich,

35
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:36,937
Kusuma's new Vice President.

36
00:04:44,147 --> 00:04:45,148
Hello, everyone.

37
00:04:46,434 --> 00:04:48,217
As you all know,

38
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:50,497
Mr. Anurak Sukontawanich,

39
00:04:51,280 --> 00:04:54,377
our former chairman is my father.

40
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:58,257
He focused on research
and developed new scent.

41
00:05:00,289 --> 00:05:01,857
After facing some health problems,

42
00:05:02,593 --> 00:05:05,930
our Kusuma brand was in haitus.

43
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:10,857
As his son, I will step
in and continue his work.

44
00:05:12,288 --> 00:05:14,337
Kusuma will launch new products.

45
00:05:15,580 --> 00:05:17,017
We will introduce our new scent

46
00:05:17,780 --> 00:05:19,897
which will be the one
and only scent in the world.

47
00:05:21,627 --> 00:05:23,437
We are now developing this new scent

48
00:05:24,494 --> 00:05:26,854
and grand press conference will be hosted
when we are ready.

49
00:05:27,654 --> 00:05:29,054
Please stay tuned for the new scent

50
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:30,981
and I will see you later.

51
00:05:32,777 --> 00:05:35,337
Good thing we didn't
host the event outdoors,

52
00:05:35,667 --> 00:05:37,113
we just lied up there and
could've been struck by lightning.

53
00:05:37,137 --> 00:05:38,617
Oh, come on.

54
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,657
We need to make it go viral.

55
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:43,937
I did what you asked me
to already, what's next?

56
00:05:44,577 --> 00:05:47,937
What do you mean by a new scent
that will change our company completely?

57
00:05:50,407 --> 00:05:51,607
Can you just calm down, Scent?

58
00:05:52,287 --> 00:05:54,297
This is your first day since you got back.

59
00:05:54,754 --> 00:05:56,817
I think you should go home and rest.

60
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:00,140
You can take care of your father as well.

61
00:06:24,584 --> 00:06:25,627
Thank you so much

62
00:06:26,647 --> 00:06:28,497
for taking care of him when I'm not around.

63
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:32,177
Your father is my elder brother.

64
00:06:32,657 --> 00:06:33,687
How can I leave him?

65
00:06:42,147 --> 00:06:43,148
Dad,

66
00:06:44,417 --> 00:06:45,457
I'm back.

67
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:47,897
I just graduated.

68
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:52,337
This time, I will be with you

69
00:06:54,647 --> 00:06:55,648
and I will not leave you.

70
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,337
Do you know why your dad became like this?

71
00:07:10,657 --> 00:07:13,617
The doctor said that his stroke was caused
from stress, wasn't it?

72
00:07:14,547 --> 00:07:15,548
Well,

73
00:07:16,577 --> 00:07:18,457
it is not just stress from work.

74
00:07:19,234 --> 00:07:20,235
There is a real reason.

75
00:07:21,474 --> 00:07:22,475
What do you mean?

76
00:07:24,057 --> 00:07:27,097
20 years ago, we lauched
a perfume called 'Bussaba',

77
00:07:28,234 --> 00:07:30,235
and it brought a good
reputation to the company.

78
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,337
It was the reason behind our wealth.

79
00:07:35,114 --> 00:07:36,115
I see.

80
00:07:36,774 --> 00:07:40,057
I was so young back then, but we
suddenly stopped producing the product.

81
00:07:42,334 --> 00:07:44,614
That was because we couldn't create
that scent any longer.

82
00:07:45,337 --> 00:07:46,338
Why was that?

83
00:07:49,334 --> 00:07:51,457
We ran out of the source to produce it.

84
00:07:52,807 --> 00:07:55,299
Your dad tried to find alternative sources.

85
00:07:56,074 --> 00:07:59,337
He had been searching for years
but he couldn't. It reached to the point

86
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:02,217
that his stress caused a
stroke five years ago.

87
00:08:03,954 --> 00:08:05,897
Where did that scent come from?

88
00:08:09,620 --> 00:08:11,021
This is the Mudan tribe.

89
00:08:11,874 --> 00:08:15,537
People from this tribe can
produce fragrance from their bodies.

90
00:08:18,027 --> 00:08:19,107
People with a fragrant smell?

91
00:08:22,674 --> 00:08:25,737
Like musk deer and small Indian civet?

92
00:08:28,259 --> 00:08:30,297
We used to have one person from Mudan.

93
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:34,297
And we extracted his body scent
to produce Bussaba perfume.

94
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:41,697
Believe it or not,

95
00:08:43,754 --> 00:08:46,057
you could make your dad's dream come true.

96
00:08:48,217 --> 00:08:49,218
It's possible that

97
00:08:50,708 --> 00:08:52,777
this could heal your dad.

98
00:09:02,857 --> 00:09:04,497
Where do the Mudan people live?

99
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:10,537
They live deep in the forest,
located on the high moutains.

100
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:13,900
They occasionally sent some of them
to sell their products in the city.

101
00:09:14,247 --> 00:09:16,937
They never introduce
where they live to anyone.

102
00:09:22,757 --> 00:09:23,758
Hello, Sun?

103
00:09:25,057 --> 00:09:26,177
I'm in Chiang Mai right now.

104
00:09:26,751 --> 00:09:28,071
What are you doing in Chiang Mai?

105
00:09:28,777 --> 00:09:32,297
Stop asking too many question,
I need you to find me a navigator.

106
00:09:33,567 --> 00:09:35,854
Navigator? Where to?

107
00:09:37,507 --> 00:09:38,508
Mudan.

108
00:09:53,794 --> 00:09:54,795
This way.

109
00:09:57,047 --> 00:09:58,048
Easy there.

110
00:10:03,554 --> 00:10:04,555
This way, sir.

111
00:10:16,914 --> 00:10:17,915
Follow me.

112
00:11:10,307 --> 00:11:11,308
Where are you heading to?

113
00:11:11,817 --> 00:11:14,018
I'm taking him to trek through the forest.

114
00:11:15,017 --> 00:11:16,937
You can't. We just found
elephants this morning.

115
00:11:17,014 --> 00:11:19,057
Well, you shouldn't step
outside the national park.

116
00:11:19,547 --> 00:11:22,060
It's dangerous and nobody
could save you in time.

117
00:11:22,314 --> 00:11:23,777
It's okay, I can take care of him.

118
00:11:24,315 --> 00:11:25,837
Please? Please, sir?

119
00:11:26,481 --> 00:11:28,201
Fine. Go ahead.

120
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:29,361
Thank you.

121
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,977
Let's go, sir.

122
00:11:31,737 --> 00:11:33,057
We're clear, follow me.

123
00:11:42,097 --> 00:11:44,737
Gaysorn.

124
00:11:48,254 --> 00:11:49,255
Gaysorn.

125
00:11:52,147 --> 00:11:53,148
Gaysorn.

126
00:11:59,354 --> 00:12:00,577
What are you doing here?

127
00:12:01,457 --> 00:12:03,097
Just sitting and thinking about things.

128
00:12:03,657 --> 00:12:04,658
Tawan,

129
00:12:05,407 --> 00:12:08,144
what does the world down there
look like? I've never seen it.

130
00:12:08,497 --> 00:12:09,627
Too hectic.

131
00:12:10,498 --> 00:12:12,578
Too many people.
It's not as comfortable as our home.

132
00:12:13,187 --> 00:12:16,557
Can you take me there next time?

133
00:12:16,737 --> 00:12:19,097
No, you can't go. Mata won't let you

134
00:12:22,297 --> 00:12:23,298
and neither will I.

135
00:12:25,057 --> 00:12:27,457
You expect me to stay on the moutain
for the rest of my life?

136
00:12:31,097 --> 00:12:32,354
You are special.

137
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:35,377
You're an heir of our tribe leader.

138
00:12:35,727 --> 00:12:37,297
What are we gonna do if you got hurt?

139
00:12:38,657 --> 00:12:41,577
There are millions of people down there
and not one of them is a good person?

140
00:12:42,060 --> 00:12:44,197
That's right. Let's go.

141
00:12:50,954 --> 00:12:52,457
I've never seen this tribe before.

142
00:12:52,889 --> 00:12:54,977
My dad used to tell
me a stories about them.

143
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,000
He said that this is the way to the tribe.

144
00:12:57,057 --> 00:12:58,058
Just follow me.

145
00:12:59,114 --> 00:13:00,115
Let's go.

146
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:21,177
Do you really know where they live?

147
00:13:22,137 --> 00:13:23,777
This way, follow me.

148
00:13:29,417 --> 00:13:31,217
Follow me, sir.

149
00:13:38,047 --> 00:13:39,607
It's about to rain, we should get back.

150
00:13:40,094 --> 00:13:42,577
You go ahead, I'll visit
my mom's house first.

151
00:14:00,294 --> 00:14:01,647
This is not good.

152
00:14:02,737 --> 00:14:04,267
It's about to rain, heavy rain.

153
00:14:05,747 --> 00:14:06,907
What's the problem with that?

154
00:14:08,167 --> 00:14:09,168
If it rains,

155
00:14:10,380 --> 00:14:11,900
the path won't be good enough to trek.

156
00:14:12,607 --> 00:14:14,817
I think we should head back.

157
00:14:15,337 --> 00:14:17,438
We can't go back, I already paid you.

158
00:14:17,737 --> 00:14:20,817
Such a waste of time, you got me walking
around in circles since the morning.

159
00:14:20,854 --> 00:14:23,097
Do you really know the
way to the Mudan tribe?

160
00:14:24,054 --> 00:14:25,377
Where exactly are the Mudan people?

161
00:14:26,234 --> 00:14:28,097
I mean… people said
they live around here.

162
00:14:28,737 --> 00:14:31,738
If it is around here, then we should go.
You took my money already.

163
00:14:32,027 --> 00:14:34,537
I'm not leaving until I see them,
or I need a refund.

164
00:14:34,937 --> 00:14:35,938
Go!

165
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,201
- I'm leaving!
- Hey!

166
00:14:43,657 --> 00:14:45,258
Hey! Hey!

167
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:50,801
Damn it!

168
00:18:18,417 --> 00:18:19,418
Your scent…

169
00:18:23,577 --> 00:18:24,578
What are you doing?

170
00:20:36,434 --> 00:20:37,435
You smell so good.

171
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:41,301
You're up?

172
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:55,481
What is that smell?

173
00:21:01,367 --> 00:21:03,387
From wildflowers.

174
00:21:05,737 --> 00:21:06,738
What kind of flower?

175
00:21:07,738 --> 00:21:08,739
I'm not familiar with it.

176
00:21:10,054 --> 00:21:11,977
You know all flower's scents.

177
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:15,168
Never mind.

178
00:21:18,770 --> 00:21:20,050
So, where are we?

179
00:21:24,787 --> 00:21:25,788
Ouch!

180
00:21:28,487 --> 00:21:29,488
Ouch!

181
00:21:33,927 --> 00:21:34,928
You should lie still.

182
00:21:36,127 --> 00:21:37,280
Tell me where am I?

183
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:39,774
This is my mom's house.

184
00:21:41,897 --> 00:21:43,577
I saw you lying down unconscious.

185
00:21:44,977 --> 00:21:47,778
What happened to you? Just stay still.

186
00:21:57,697 --> 00:21:58,857
I fell off the mountain.

187
00:22:02,794 --> 00:22:03,795
Well..

188
00:22:05,907 --> 00:22:07,537
I'll get you new clothes to change into.

189
00:22:08,426 --> 00:22:09,427
Just lie down.

190
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:36,881
Let me help.

191
00:24:22,437 --> 00:24:23,538
That nice smell again.

192
00:24:29,737 --> 00:24:30,738
What are you doing?

193
00:24:31,294 --> 00:24:32,857
I smell it from you.

194
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,601
You mean from this?

195
00:24:37,354 --> 00:24:38,355
No.

196
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:46,761
Let me heal your wound.

197
00:25:11,857 --> 00:25:12,858
Where do you come from?

198
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:15,641
I'm from the city.

199
00:25:17,977 --> 00:25:21,528
I followed the huntsman to the forest.

200
00:25:23,047 --> 00:25:25,857
What were you doing in the forest?

201
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:29,177
I'm looking for someone.

202
00:25:30,852 --> 00:25:33,369
Have you ever heard of the Mudan tribe?

203
00:25:37,697 --> 00:25:38,857
You've heard about it, right?

204
00:25:42,714 --> 00:25:43,715
Nope.

205
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:47,097
Mudan people produce
fragrance from their bodies.

206
00:25:47,540 --> 00:25:49,060
People say that they live around here.

207
00:25:50,537 --> 00:25:52,177
- You know them?
- There is no such thing.

208
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:55,960
People producing fragrance
from the bodies? It's a myth.

209
00:26:00,280 --> 00:26:01,281
You should rest.

210
00:26:02,747 --> 00:26:04,667
When you get better, I'll lead
you to the edge of the forest.

211
00:26:05,777 --> 00:26:06,778
So you can go home.

212
00:26:06,967 --> 00:26:08,007
You will come back, right?

213
00:26:09,627 --> 00:26:10,867
I'll find you something to eat.

214
00:26:21,027 --> 00:26:22,457
I talked to the police,

215
00:26:22,614 --> 00:26:24,854
they found the huntsman that
took Scent to the forest but

216
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,777
he lost Scent after the heavy rain.

217
00:26:28,414 --> 00:26:29,415
What the hell?

218
00:26:29,994 --> 00:26:32,017
He left his boss in the
middle of the forest?

219
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:36,841
Don't worry.

220
00:26:37,467 --> 00:26:40,217
I'll fly there tomorrow
morning to look for him.

221
00:26:40,754 --> 00:26:41,755
Good.

222
00:26:41,947 --> 00:26:43,737
You are his one and only best friend,

223
00:26:43,914 --> 00:26:44,977
please look for him.

224
00:26:54,377 --> 00:26:55,378
Are you done with this?

225
00:26:56,967 --> 00:26:59,067
Smells so good, can I get one?

226
00:27:00,220 --> 00:27:02,977
- Gaysorn, where are you?
- Uncle?

227
00:27:03,094 --> 00:27:05,214
Have you seen my clothes?
I hung them here last night.

228
00:27:05,337 --> 00:27:07,297
Gaysorn, where are you?

229
00:27:08,027 --> 00:27:09,028
Gaysorn.

230
00:27:09,140 --> 00:27:11,060
Who are you yelling for?

231
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,177
Have you seen Gaysorn?

232
00:27:13,694 --> 00:27:15,217
I haven't.

233
00:27:15,857 --> 00:27:18,137
He could've gone to the
forest to get some food.

234
00:27:19,257 --> 00:27:20,837
To the forest or to the city.

235
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:24,721
What did you say?

236
00:27:25,654 --> 00:27:27,655
He told me that he
wanted to go to the city.

237
00:27:28,580 --> 00:27:29,582
He can't.

238
00:27:29,714 --> 00:27:32,217
You need to find him now, he can't go.

239
00:27:33,854 --> 00:27:34,855
Let's go!

240
00:27:35,734 --> 00:27:36,935
What is wrong with you?

241
00:28:53,740 --> 00:28:54,741
Hey.

242
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:03,457
You're up?

243
00:29:06,314 --> 00:29:07,437
The air is so pure here.

244
00:29:08,614 --> 00:29:11,197
I can smell flowers, grass,

245
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:15,041
even the dew.

246
00:29:18,134 --> 00:29:19,137
Your nose works so well.

247
00:29:20,297 --> 00:29:22,617
Sure, I do. I work in perf…

248
00:29:29,127 --> 00:29:30,237
My name is Scent.

249
00:29:38,777 --> 00:29:42,457
Thank you for saving my life.

250
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:48,601
Gaysorn.

251
00:29:50,477 --> 00:29:51,578
Gaysorn? Like pollen?

252
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:55,501
It's a woman's name.

253
00:29:57,394 --> 00:29:58,577
Flowers are flowers.

254
00:29:59,747 --> 00:30:01,217
They are genderless.

255
00:30:05,214 --> 00:30:06,215
You're right.

256
00:30:07,177 --> 00:30:09,497
Flowers are flowers.

257
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:27,721
I smell it again.

258
00:30:34,414 --> 00:30:35,415
It smells so nice.

259
00:30:39,340 --> 00:30:41,140
I've never smelled
anything like this before.

260
00:30:45,707 --> 00:30:47,708
- Are you sure it's not from you?
- Let's eat.

261
00:30:49,894 --> 00:30:51,054
I prepared something for you.

262
00:31:00,577 --> 00:31:04,217
People from this tribe can
produce fragrance from their bodies.

263
00:31:04,697 --> 00:31:06,777
You need to pay attention to people
and the surroundings.

264
00:31:18,587 --> 00:31:19,588
Can you eat it?

265
00:31:22,427 --> 00:31:23,428
I think so.

266
00:31:43,147 --> 00:31:45,520
This chili paste smells
good too. From what?

267
00:31:48,374 --> 00:31:49,375
It's Ma Kuang.

268
00:31:49,854 --> 00:31:52,377
You really have good nose,
are you sure you're not a dog?

269
00:32:15,574 --> 00:32:18,457
Are you sure you don't
know the Mudan tribe?

270
00:32:21,474 --> 00:32:22,475
Gaysorn.

271
00:32:23,547 --> 00:32:24,548
Gaysorn.

272
00:32:25,567 --> 00:32:26,568
Gaysorn.

273
00:32:28,337 --> 00:32:29,338
Gaysorn.

274
00:32:30,667 --> 00:32:31,668
What?

275
00:32:31,967 --> 00:32:32,968
- What?
- Gaysorn!

276
00:32:33,234 --> 00:32:34,235
- Hey.
- Listen.

277
00:32:34,507 --> 00:32:35,697
- Gaysorn.
- Be quiet.

278
00:32:35,914 --> 00:32:38,297
- Don't say anything and don't go outside.
- What?

279
00:32:39,547 --> 00:32:40,548
Gaysorn.

280
00:32:45,534 --> 00:32:46,535
Tawan.

281
00:32:48,377 --> 00:32:49,378
Is everything okay?

282
00:32:51,714 --> 00:32:54,017
Mata asked me to look
for you, where were you?

283
00:32:56,607 --> 00:32:57,994
I… well…

284
00:32:58,347 --> 00:33:00,107
I went to get mushrooms
and some vegetables.

285
00:33:00,594 --> 00:33:01,697
Why?

286
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:05,337
She was worried that
you would go down there,

287
00:33:06,180 --> 00:33:07,181
and so was I.

288
00:33:09,894 --> 00:33:12,337
Tawan, I'm an adult.

289
00:33:13,497 --> 00:33:15,977
I can walk and go wherever I want to.

290
00:33:18,514 --> 00:33:19,515
Gaysorn.

291
00:33:20,227 --> 00:33:21,228
Gaysorn.

292
00:33:42,347 --> 00:33:43,348
Is everything okay?

293
00:33:44,034 --> 00:33:45,035
Yeah.

294
00:33:46,374 --> 00:33:47,375
Liar.

295
00:33:48,474 --> 00:33:50,874
If it was really nothing,
why did you ask me to hide in here?

296
00:33:51,767 --> 00:33:53,217
They are not fond of strangers.

297
00:33:55,777 --> 00:33:59,057
If they found out that I brought an
outsider here, they wouldn't be pleased.

298
00:34:04,660 --> 00:34:05,980
Are you trying to hide something?

299
00:34:07,157 --> 00:34:08,158
Planting opium poppies?

300
00:34:09,134 --> 00:34:10,135
Drug dealers?

301
00:34:16,137 --> 00:34:17,138
I was just kidding.

302
00:34:17,937 --> 00:34:20,617
But if there is really nothing,
why are you afraid of the outsiders?

303
00:34:24,094 --> 00:34:25,614
What's wrong with being the outsiders?

304
00:34:40,980 --> 00:34:41,981
I mean...

305
00:34:42,837 --> 00:34:44,138
My mom went to the city

306
00:34:45,726 --> 00:34:47,686
and she disappeared.
She never come back here.

307
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:51,657
Disappeared? Like completely gone?

308
00:34:52,257 --> 00:34:54,434
That's right. More than 10 years now.

309
00:34:55,057 --> 00:34:57,857
She didn't come back.
She didn't send any letters.

310
00:34:58,874 --> 00:35:00,137
Nobody knew where she was

311
00:35:01,377 --> 00:35:02,779
or how she was doing.

312
00:35:07,787 --> 00:35:09,747
Mata said that my mom
went there to rescue my dad

313
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:12,897
but she didn't come back.

314
00:35:13,907 --> 00:35:15,437
Mata believed that

315
00:35:16,908 --> 00:35:18,637
people there could…

316
00:35:32,177 --> 00:35:33,178
My deepest condolences.

317
00:35:41,907 --> 00:35:43,937
Mata said that my mom
wouldn't come back here.

318
00:35:47,497 --> 00:35:49,198
But I hope that she is still alive

319
00:35:52,654 --> 00:35:54,297
somewhere in this world.

320
00:36:06,974 --> 00:36:08,974
Every family has to deal
with something difficult.

321
00:36:11,214 --> 00:36:12,217
My dad is still alive.

322
00:36:14,977 --> 00:36:15,978
But he is bedridden

323
00:36:17,017 --> 00:36:18,377
like a puppet who can breathe.

324
00:36:19,457 --> 00:36:20,737
He can't talk.

325
00:36:23,557 --> 00:36:24,558
What are you going to do?

326
00:36:25,740 --> 00:36:29,381
I will do whatever it takes
to bring him back to normal.

327
00:36:34,814 --> 00:36:36,215
And I will find my mom.

328
00:36:43,457 --> 00:36:44,658
It will come true one day,

329
00:36:45,754 --> 00:36:46,755
right?

330
00:37:09,974 --> 00:37:10,975
- Wow!
- Oh my!

331
00:37:11,737 --> 00:37:12,977
- It's huge!
- So huge!

332
00:37:19,854 --> 00:37:20,855
Get it up here.

333
00:37:24,100 --> 00:37:25,840
Wait.

334
00:37:26,297 --> 00:37:27,857
Where is Gaysorn? He's not joining us?

335
00:37:30,154 --> 00:37:31,155
I'm here.

336
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:38,017
Malee. Renu.

337
00:37:38,187 --> 00:37:39,188
Gaysorn.

338
00:37:39,300 --> 00:37:40,780
I wish you two stay together forever.

339
00:37:42,080 --> 00:37:43,081
Thank you so much.

340
00:37:43,944 --> 00:37:46,977
When you get married,

341
00:37:47,307 --> 00:37:49,837
Malee and I will give it back to you.

342
00:37:52,615 --> 00:37:54,817
- Come on, let me help you.
- Sure.

343
00:37:55,240 --> 00:37:57,257
Come to think of it,

344
00:37:57,777 --> 00:38:00,457
Seeing these two getting married

345
00:38:00,697 --> 00:38:03,298
makes me want to get married
as well. Isn't it right, Tawan?

346
00:38:09,947 --> 00:38:12,467
Tawan, don't forget to tell us
when you decided to get married.

347
00:38:14,337 --> 00:38:16,338
Gaysorn, are you blushing?

348
00:38:43,180 --> 00:38:44,181
Gaysorn.

349
00:38:48,580 --> 00:38:49,582
Thank you.

350
00:38:56,580 --> 00:38:58,007
Are you thinking about your mom?

351
00:39:01,207 --> 00:39:02,208
Mata,

352
00:39:04,254 --> 00:39:05,255
can I ask you something?

353
00:39:08,447 --> 00:39:11,057
Some of us went down
there to search for your mom.

354
00:39:12,434 --> 00:39:13,977
But no one heard anything about her.

355
00:39:18,060 --> 00:39:20,457
Your mom went to
Bangkok and the city is huge.

356
00:39:20,634 --> 00:39:22,257
How can we find her?

357
00:39:28,214 --> 00:39:31,215
I don't want to say it but I have to.

358
00:39:32,967 --> 00:39:34,817
It's been more than 10 years.

359
00:39:35,674 --> 00:39:37,457
If she was still alive,

360
00:39:39,097 --> 00:39:41,337
she would come back to
you for sure, don't you think?

361
00:39:45,617 --> 00:39:48,837
We circle back to
this conclusion every time.

362
00:39:51,327 --> 00:39:52,328
Gaysorn!

363
00:39:54,780 --> 00:39:57,577
Can you help us here?

364
00:39:58,487 --> 00:39:59,508
Sure.

365
00:40:00,287 --> 00:40:01,288
I should go.

366
00:40:13,330 --> 00:40:17,130
I feel bad for him. I mean, that's his mom.

367
00:40:18,257 --> 00:40:19,417
You can't go soft.

368
00:40:21,627 --> 00:40:22,857
If you really love him,

369
00:40:24,027 --> 00:40:26,497
you can't let him go down there, ever.

370
00:40:50,114 --> 00:40:52,057
Hey! Where do you think you're going?

371
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:54,441
Get back inside.

372
00:40:56,140 --> 00:40:58,260
You want me to stay in the
cottage all day and night?

373
00:40:58,900 --> 00:41:01,417
- I already told you…
- That I can't let anyone see me.

374
00:41:01,977 --> 00:41:04,937
I'm well aware of that
and this is during the night.

375
00:41:06,187 --> 00:41:09,067
Your cottage is situated so far from
the village, who would see me here?

376
00:41:10,517 --> 00:41:13,537
Well, can you take me to stargazing?

377
00:41:15,740 --> 00:41:18,977
I want to see how pretty
the stars can be from up here.

378
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:22,321
Please.

379
00:41:22,947 --> 00:41:26,177
Please! Come on, Gaysorn.

380
00:41:43,500 --> 00:41:44,501
What about Bangkok?

381
00:41:47,427 --> 00:41:48,428
Is it far from here?

382
00:41:51,029 --> 00:41:52,869
Why did you ask? Do
you want to go to Bangkok?

383
00:41:55,837 --> 00:41:58,577
Well… maybe.

384
00:42:01,800 --> 00:42:03,560
I just want to know
how far it is from here.

385
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:11,497
It's about the same distance
from here to Chiang Mai,

386
00:42:12,497 --> 00:42:13,498
multiplied by five.

387
00:42:18,817 --> 00:42:19,818
What?

388
00:42:20,820 --> 00:42:22,940
Don't tell me that you have
never been to Chiang Mai.

389
00:42:23,497 --> 00:42:24,698
I've never been anywhere.

390
00:42:26,314 --> 00:42:27,315
Are you kidding me?

391
00:42:32,497 --> 00:42:33,737
I want to go to Bangkok.

392
00:42:35,720 --> 00:42:36,857
I want to look for my mom.

393
00:42:50,940 --> 00:42:51,941
Gaysorn.

394
00:42:53,177 --> 00:42:54,178
Gaysorn.

395
00:42:56,227 --> 00:42:58,619
Renu and Malee asked you
to secure these fabric's ends.

396
00:43:00,020 --> 00:43:01,021
Gaysorn.

397
00:43:02,440 --> 00:43:03,441
Gaysorn.

398
00:43:08,607 --> 00:43:09,608
He is not here.

399
00:43:10,847 --> 00:43:12,897
He went back here already. Where is he now?

400
00:43:22,707 --> 00:43:24,987
Hey! Did you hear that?

401
00:43:25,737 --> 00:43:28,217
What is that sound? Someone is coming?

402
00:43:31,500 --> 00:43:33,177
We need to hide. Come on!

403
00:43:37,537 --> 00:43:38,538
What is it?

404
00:44:04,107 --> 00:44:05,108
That smell.

405
00:44:08,747 --> 00:44:10,537
I think I smell it from…

406
00:44:24,457 --> 00:44:25,458
That sound is gone.

407
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:27,585
We should go.

408
00:44:39,454 --> 00:44:40,555
Who are you?

409
00:44:53,700 --> 00:44:56,060
(Next Episode) I'm just a tourist
who got lost in the woods.

410
00:44:56,085 --> 00:44:56,416
You're lying!

411
00:44:59,283 --> 00:45:01,202
- There’s a fire!
- Quick, get some water!

412
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:03,879
We don't even know what happened to Mom.

413
00:45:03,880 --> 00:45:05,330
Maybe she's still alive.

414
00:45:05,331 --> 00:45:06,240
Is that why you're helping him?

415
00:45:06,241 --> 00:45:08,920
You just want to hang out with them, right?

416
00:45:10,711 --> 00:45:12,011
I just want to be your friend.

417
00:45:12,020 --> 00:45:13,651
You can't trust outsiders.

418
00:45:13,675 --> 00:45:14,675
But I trust him.

419
00:45:20,361 --> 00:45:21,509
Come to Bangkok with me.

420
00:45:21,711 --> 00:45:24,818
If you want to find your mother,
I'll help you.
